Name: Finland 10-year Government Bonds (with GFD Extension)
Periodicity:
Annual From Dec 1889 To Dec 1899
Monthly From Jan 1900 To Mar 1990
Daily From Apr 1990 To Nov 2021
Metadata:
Source: Finlands Bank
Notes: The 3.5% Grand Duchy of Finland bonds traded in Amsterdam from 1889 to 1895 and in Berlin from December 1896 to February 1909 (BGFIN35R-BE) are used, and the 4.5% Grand Duchy of Finland Railroad Bonds (BGFIN45-LO) are used from April 1909 through February 1924. The Finland 6s of 1945 (BGFIN645) as quoted in New York are used from March 1924 through December 1945, the Helsingfors 6.5% municipal bonds of 1960 are used for 1946 through 1948, and the Finland 5s of 1961 are used through 1953. No data are available from November 1953 through 19r59. The current series covers central government taxable bonds of more than five years. Data are annual for 1960 through 1965, and quarterly from 1966 until 1971
The benchmark bond is used for this series. The benchmark bond is the bond that is closest to the stated maturity without exceeding it. When the government issues a new bond of the stated maturity, it replaces the bond used for the index to keep the maturity as close to the stated time period as possible. Depending on how much of a difference there is in maturities, there may be some adjustment in the yield when the new bond is introduced.
